<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Clean, Inspect, Measure, and Test - Cylinder Head Pressure Test
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Cylinder Head Pressure Test</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Pressure testing the cylinder head will reveal cracks in ports or sleeve leakage which can not be
                    seen using dye penetrant.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_321.xml" xrefid="s1318">Remove valves from cylinder head</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s1318"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_180.xml" xrefid="s0716">Install fuel injectors</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0716"/>
                in cylinder head injector bores.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350013367" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figZTS/ZTSE4289A_4647_4648.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Cylinder head pressure test tools</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder Head Test Plate</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water Supply Housing Pressure Adapter</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thermostat Opening Pressure Adapter</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pressure test cylinder head using
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_341.xml" xrefid="t335001303">Cylinder Head Test Plate, Water Supply Housing
                    Pressure Adapter, Thermostat Opening Pressure Adapter, and a pressure regulator
                </hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001303"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach Cylinder Head Test Plate to cylinder head gasket surface using mounting bolts and
                nuts supplied with kit.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach Water Supply Housing Pressure Adaptor to cylinder head and secure with mounting
                bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove thermostat and fill cylinder head with hot water.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach Thermostat Opening Pressure Adapter to cylinder head and secure with mounting
                bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach compressed air hose and pressure regulator to hose fitting on Thermostat Opening
                Pressure Adapter.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 124 to 138 kPa (18 to 20 psi) air pressure and inspect cylinder head for leaks. Check
                the following:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel injector nozzle sleeve areas</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Valve ports</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Upper deck</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Lower deck</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <para>If leakage is observed from any fuel injector nozzle sleeves, replace injector sleeves and pressure test
            cylinder head again. If cylinder head leakage is observed replace the cylinder head.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
